\pard\f0\fs28 Leaves opposite, scale-like, connate in pairs, forming a sheath around the stem. Perianth in 1 whorl. Male flowers solitary, sessile. Perianth 2- to 5-lobed. Stamens sessile; anthers dehiscing transversely. Female flowers solitary or in pairs, pedicellate; perianth of 2 short teeth. Fruit green, dry, dehiscing explosively. ({\i Razoumofskya} Hoffm.)
\par

