\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 1.            Asarum}                   L.
\par     

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By P.W. Ball & J.R. Akeroyd
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Herbs with creeping rhizome. Flowers solitary and terminal. Perianth actinomorphic, 3-lobed, persistent in fruit. Stamens 12, in 2 whorls, free or almost so; filaments short. Fruit subglobose, dehiscing irregularly.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Literature: I. Kukkonen & P. Uotila,{\i  Ann. Bot. Fenn. }{\b 14:} 131-142 (1977).
\par

